            <div class="project-info">
                <div class="project-name">Management & Plastic Recycling</div>
                <div class="project-description">
                    <div class="initial-solutions">
                        <p>Implement comprehensive collection systems that encourage segregation of plastic waste at the
                            source (homes, businesses, public places). Provide easily accessible recycling bins and
                            educate the public on the importance of separating recyclables.</p>
                        <p>Invest in advanced sorting technologies that can efficiently separate different types of
                            plastics. Use automated systems like infrared sorting, robotics, and AI to improve the
                            accuracy and efficiency of sorting.</p>
                        <p>Implement EPR policies that make manufacturers responsible for the entire lifecycle of their
                            products, including post-consumer phase. Encourage manufacturers to design products that are
                            easier to recycle and to take back their products for recycling.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div id="moreSolutionsPlastic" class="more-solutions-hidden">
                        <p>Launch public awareness campaigns to educate citizens about the importance of recycling and
                            how to properly dispose of plastic waste. Partner with schools, community groups, and
                            businesses to promote recycling initiatives.</p>
                        <p>Create incentive programs that reward individuals and businesses for recycling plastic. Offer
                            monetary rewards, discounts, or other incentives for returning plastic bottles and
                            containers.</p>
                        <p>Encourage partnerships between governments, NGOs, and private companies to improve plastic
                            recycling infrastructure. Collaborate with businesses to develop innovative recycling
                            solutions and market for recycled products.</p>
                        <p>Enforce strict regulations on plastic production and waste management to reduce plastic waste
                            and promote recycling. Ban single-use plastics and promote the use of recyclable and
                            biodegradable alternatives.</p>
                        <p>Invest in research and development to find new and more efficient ways to recycle plastic.
                            Support innovations in creating biodegradable plastics and alternatives to traditional
                            plastics.</p>
                        <p>Promote the design and use of reusable products to minimize plastic waste. Companies can
                            create durable and multi-use items instead of single-use plastics. Consumers can be
                            encouraged to use reusable bags, bottles, and containers through awareness campaigns and
                            incentives.</p>
                        <p>Implement and support circular economy models where plastic products are designed to be
                            reused, refurbished, or recycled continuously. This reduces the need for new plastic
                            production and minimizes waste.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
