                <div class="project-name">Biodiversity & Afforestation</div>
                <div class="project-description">
                    <div class="initial-solutions">
                        <p>Protect Natural Habitats: Implement measures to protect existing natural habitats, including
                            forests, wetlands, grasslands, and marine ecosystems. Establish protected areas and wildlife
                            reserves to conserve biodiversity and provide safe habitats for endangered species.</p>
                        <p>Promote Reforestation Projects: Launch reforestation projects to restore degraded land and
                            increase forest cover. Plant native tree species to enhance local biodiversity and support
                            ecosystem services such as water regulation, soil stabilization, and carbon sequestration.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div id="moreSolutionsBiodiversity" class="more-solutions-hidden">
                        <p>Support Sustainable Land Management Practices: Encourage sustainable land management
                            practices that balance ecological health with human needs. This includes agroforestry,
                            sustainable agriculture, and silvopasture systems that integrate trees with crops and
                            livestock.</p>
                        <p>Encourage Biodiversity-Friendly Agriculture: Promote agricultural practices that support
                            biodiversity, such as organic farming, crop rotation, and the use of natural pest control
                            methods. These practices help maintain soil health, protect pollinators, and reduce the
                            environmental impact of farming.
                        </p>
                        <p>Restore degraded ecosystems to bring back their ecological functions and services.</p>
                        <p>Promote Urban Green Spaces: Develop and maintain green spaces in urban areas, such as parks,
                            green roofs, and community gardens. Urban green spaces provide habitats for wildlife,
                            improve air quality, and offer recreational opportunities for residents.
                        </p>
                        <p>Foster Community Participation in Conservation: Engage local communities in conservation
                            efforts through education, awareness campaigns, and participatory projects. Empowering
                            communities to take an active role in biodiversity conservation ensures long-term
                            sustainability and local stewardship.</p>
                        <p>Implement Policy and Legislation for Conservation: Advocate for strong policies and
                            legislation to protect biodiversity and promote afforestation. This includes enforcing laws
                            against illegal logging, promoting sustainable forestry practices, and providing incentives
                            for conservation activities.
                        </p>
                    </div>
